[{"id":"VR857505","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div><div class=\"stimulus_reference\"><div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows two rays labeled Ray 1 and Ray 2 traveling in parallel from the left side of the figure and below the principal axis. Ray 1 is mid way between the principal axis and bottom edge of the lens. Ray 2 is further down closer to the bottom edge of the lens. Both rays pass through a convex lens. Ray 1 travels up and to the right and crosses the principal axis at a point labeled P sub 1. The distance between the lens and P sub 1 is labeled d. Ray 2 stops at the lens.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/578/VR857505.g01.svg\"/></div></div></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">Two rays are incident on a convex lens, as shown in the figure. Both rays are initially parallel to the principal axis of the lens. Ray <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1\"><math alttext=\"1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1</mn></math></span></span> then crosses the principal axis at point <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"P sub 1\"><math alttext=\"P sub 1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math></span></span>, which is a distance <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"d\"><math alttext=\"d\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>d</mi></math></span></span> from the lens. If Ray <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn></math></span></span> is initially twice as far from the principal axis as Ray <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1\"><math alttext=\"1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1</mn></math></span></span>, how far from the lens is point <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"P sub 2\"><math alttext=\"P sub 2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math></span></span>, the location where Ray <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn></math></span></span> crosses the principal axis?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VR857505_rubric","choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"P sub 2\"><math alttext=\"P sub 2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math></span></span> is a distance <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"d over 2\"><math alttext=\"d over 2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mfrac><mi>d</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math></span></span> from the lens.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"P sub 2\"><math alttext=\"P sub 2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math></span></span> is a distance <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"d\"><math alttext=\"d\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>d</mi></math></span></span> from the lens.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"P sub 2\"><math alttext=\"P sub 2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math></span></span> is a distance <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2 d\"><math alttext=\"2 d\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn><mi>d</mi></math></span></span> from the lens.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"P sub 2\"><math alttext=\"P sub 2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math></span></span> is greater than a distance of <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2 d\"><math alttext=\"2 d\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn><mi>d</mi></math></span></span> from the lens.</p>"],"answer":1}]